<!--
https://forum.shotcut.org/t/filter-sets-flip-horizontal-transition/40486

How to use:
	Create a 1-second transition between 2 clips. Preferably on track V1
	Select the transition clip.
	Go to the Properties panel.
	Choose the Cut option, and set Position at 50%
	Go to Filters > Sets
	Select the Flip-Horizontal filter set.

Notes:
I have set background behind the animation to black.
If you want to use a different color, edit the Background Color parameter of the Size, Position & Rotate filter If the transition is on any other track than track V1,
AND
if there is content (video, image, color clip) directly below the transition, you will need to set the Background Color parameter to transparent (Alpha channel = 0)

-->
